      <dsc>
         <c id="ref8" level="series">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Inventory</unittitle>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_afba53f16e2a954c4e471af55d5bfa4e">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The Facsimiles of Autographs and of Famous Documents Collection is used primarily by Manuscripts and Archives staff to identify or verify signatures found in other collections. The facsimiles are printed or photostatic copies of the originals unless otherwise noted. The dates given are the dates of the reproductions, not of the originals. Folder 2 was given by George Shea, and folder 5 by Mrs. Perle Ward in November 1940. Folder 6 came either from Mrs. Ward in November 1940, or from Rev. W.H. Owen in January 1934. The provenance of the other items is unknown.</p>
            </scopecontent>
